Thunbergia
============

Black-eyed Susan
-----------------

Use thunbergia to brighten up arches and fences or to cascade from large hanging baskets. These quick growing climbers flower from mid-summer until autumn, when killed by the frost. Some make good conservatory plants.

150 Species, native to tropical and subtropical regions of sub-Saharan Africa, Madagascar, southern Asia, New Guinea, and Australia

vigorous annual or perennial vines and shrubs growing to 2â€“8 m tall

Classification
----------------

 - Common Names: black-eyed Susan vine or black-eyed Susan
 - Family: Acanthaceae
 - Variety: alata

